This paper discusses the use of machine learning and real-time control for network management, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of learning for inference and prediction, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of networks driving themselves involves control systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the importance of security, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of networks, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
